Progresso Plain Panko Bread Crumbs create a light and crispy coating that is perfect for chicken, pork or fish. Progresso Panko Crispy Bread Crumbs is a Japanese style bread crumb. Create meals that are truly memorable with Progresso premium quality ingredients.

Directions
Basic Preparation: 2 tbsp flour; 1/2 tsp salt; 1/4 tsp pepper; 1 egg, beaten; 1 cup Progresso plain panko bread crumbs; 4 boneless skinless chicken breasts (pounded or sliced to 1/2-inch thickness); 2 tbsp oil or butter.
1. Place flour, egg and bread crumbs on separate plates.
2. Mix salt and pepper into flour.
3. Coat chicken with flour mixture, dip in egg, coat well with bread crumbs.
4. In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
5. Cook chicken in oil 8-10 minutes, turning once, until thickest part is 165 degrees F and coating is golden brown. Baking Option (for fish, chicken or pork): Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray baking dish. Follow steps 1-3 above. Bake fish 15-20 minutes or until it flakes easily with fork. Bake chicken or pork 20-30 minutes, until thickest part of chicken is 165 degrees F and pork is no longer pink in center. Flavor Boost: Replace the flour and egg in step 1 with one of your favorite sauces, such as honey mustard or barbeque sauce, mixed with a little mayonnaise. Coat with bread crumbs. 4 servings.

Prep Time: 5 minutes Cook Times: 20 minutes Makes 6 servings. You Will Need: 1 pkg. McCormick Cooking Bag & Seasoning Mix, 6 bone-in or boneless pork chops, 3/4-inch thick (about 2-1/2 lbs), 1/4 cup water. Directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Arrange opened Cooking Bag in 13x9-inch baking pan or dish. Trim excess fat from pork chops. Sprinkle Seasoning Mix evenly on both sides of each pork chop. Place in single layer in Bag. 2. Pour water over pork chops. Close Bag loosely with nylon tie. Cut 4 small holes in top of Bag to allow steam to escape. 3. Bake in lower half of oven 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Let stand 5 minutes. Cut open Bag. If desired, serve with McCormick Pork Gravy. For Pork Roast: Bake 2 lbs. boneless pork roast 45 minutes. Bake 3 lbs. bone-in pork roast 1-1/4 hours. Important: Allow 8 inches for Bag to expand while cooking. Cooking Bag should not touch oven walls or racks.
